[thinking] **Analyzing method access in Java**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering how to access private methods in Java. It seems that `findVirtual` might not work, but `findSpecial` could be the solution. `findSpecial` takes into account the `callerClass`, which can invoke superclass method implementations. If I'm checking private interface methods, it seems `findVirtual` could fail while `findSpecial` succeeds. Also, I wonder how we would invoke private interface methods and what role `MethodHandle` plays in all of this. Let's explore!
